# Windows Build Environment (MSYS2 UCRT64)

## Parallelism (all agents, all platforms)

Always build with **`make -j8`**. Do not run bare `make` when compiling the game or verifying C++ changes.

- Windows: `.\scripts\Invoke-Ucrt64.ps1 "cd src && make -j8"`
- Linux / macOS / MSYS2 shell: `cd src && make -j8`

## Windows shell wrapper

On Windows, the agent shell is PowerShell. Do **not** run `make`, `gcc`, or `scripts/*.sh` directly in PowerShell.

Run native C++ builds and bash scripts through MSYS2 **UCRT64** using the repo wrapper from the repo root:

```powershell
.\scripts\Invoke-Ucrt64.ps1 "cd src && make -j8"
.\scripts\Invoke-Ucrt64.ps1 "cd src && make run"
.\scripts\Invoke-Ucrt64.ps1 "./scripts/compile-commands.sh"
.\scripts\Invoke-Ucrt64.ps1 "./scripts/update-translations.sh"
```

`scripts/Invoke-Ucrt64.ps1` auto-detects MSYS2 (`C:\msys64`, `C:\msys2`, `C:\progs\msys2`, Scoop/Chocolatey paths, or `msys2_shell.cmd` on PATH). Override with `MSYS2_ROOT` if needed.

For gdb / clangd, point at `$env:MSYS2_ROOT\ucrt64\bin` (see `.vscode/launch.json`, which uses `${env:MSYS2_ROOT}`).
